00:23:16.640 --> 00:23:19.090
And one of the things that
happens with any interface

00:23:19.090 --> 00:23:22.181
if you're interacting with it
is you're injecting energy.

00:23:22.181 --> 00:23:22.680
Right?

00:23:22.680 --> 00:23:24.460
There's events that are
happening where you're either

00:23:24.460 --> 00:23:26.820
interacting with it, you're
touching the interface,

00:23:26.820 --> 00:23:29.384
and as you're using it
you're injecting energy

00:23:29.384 --> 00:23:31.300
into the process so
things that are happening.

00:23:31.300 --> 00:23:32.883
And one of the most
fundamental things

00:23:32.883 --> 00:23:36.240
that happens within physics is
that whenever a signal happens,

00:23:36.240 --> 00:23:38.660
whether it's sound, or
light, or what have you,

00:23:38.660 --> 00:23:40.230
it propagates in a circle.

00:23:40.230 --> 00:23:42.440
It propagates from
its point of origin,

00:23:42.440 --> 00:23:45.729
at ideally at the same
velocity outwards, right?

00:23:45.729 --> 00:23:48.020
And that's generally in a
sphere in a constrained depth

00:23:48.020 --> 00:23:49.853
environment, that's
going to be in a circle.

00:23:49.853 --> 00:23:51.530
And so when you see
not only the circles

00:23:51.530 --> 00:23:54.350
in terms of the affordance
for interacting,

00:23:54.350 --> 00:23:57.890
but also as you tap on things
and that circle radiates,

00:23:57.890 --> 00:24:02.030
it's really about just conveying
the sense of the physicality

00:24:02.030 --> 00:24:03.649
of the energy going
into this system,

00:24:03.649 --> 00:24:05.190
and that that's
actually your actions

00:24:05.190 --> 00:24:07.260
are spreading forth
into communicating

00:24:07.260 --> 00:24:10.920
with the rest of the things
that are on the screen.

