00:27:17.480 --> 00:27:19.630
CHRISTIAN ROBERTSON: Yeah,
so I think one of the things

00:27:19.630 --> 00:27:22.005
to know about-- This isn't
just true of motion design.

00:27:22.005 --> 00:27:25.080
It's true of design
generally, that there's

00:27:25.080 --> 00:27:28.010
a lot that's going on
below what people notice.

00:27:28.010 --> 00:27:30.330
So we don't actually
want people all the time

00:27:30.330 --> 00:27:32.050
thinking about the
animations when

00:27:32.050 --> 00:27:34.000
they're going from
one state to another.

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:36.450
We don't want them
to say, gee whiz,

00:27:36.450 --> 00:27:39.590
I just opened up that email,
and again I saw that animation.

00:27:39.590 --> 00:27:41.530
We want them thinking
about the email.

00:27:41.530 --> 00:27:45.160
So if you apply that
standard is how much do

00:27:45.160 --> 00:27:47.410
I want people thinking about
the animation themselves,

00:27:47.410 --> 00:27:49.440
what is it trying
to communicate, then

00:27:49.440 --> 00:27:52.434
you can kind of back it
down to the right level.

00:27:52.434 --> 00:27:53.850
NICHOLAS JITKOF:
One of the things

00:27:53.850 --> 00:27:56.370
that we considered consistently
throughout this process

00:27:56.370 --> 00:27:59.480
was how to use the animation
to sort of go along

00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:01.080
with user's intention.

00:28:01.080 --> 00:28:03.750
Because when you have touch
responses that sort of emanate

00:28:03.750 --> 00:28:07.530
outwards it's very easy to hide
details in there that reinforce

00:28:07.530 --> 00:28:09.460
what's happening without
feeling like you've

00:28:09.460 --> 00:28:10.990
added a bunch of
animation in there.

00:28:10.990 --> 00:28:14.670
So we're going to go into
this a bit more tomorrow,

00:28:14.670 --> 00:28:16.952
but having things
sort of move counter

00:28:16.952 --> 00:28:18.660
to the direction the
user's doing things,

00:28:18.660 --> 00:28:19.670
draw attention to them.

00:28:19.670 --> 00:28:20.440
And if you're
going to do so, you

00:28:20.440 --> 00:28:21.687
should do that intentionally.

00:28:21.687 --> 00:28:23.520
If you don't want
intention drawn to things,

00:28:23.520 --> 00:28:24.620
there's places to hide them.

00:28:24.620 --> 00:28:26.040
And it's really about
trying to figure out

00:28:26.040 --> 00:28:27.581
how you want to
balance it, and where

00:28:27.581 --> 00:28:30.880
you want to draw
people's attention.

